Heinz Diehl wrote:
>Have you tried to disable the "CPU to PCI write buffer" option in
>the BIOS ? On many systems this has been the point of failure.
Disabling "CPU to PCI write buffer" in my VA-503+ FIC Via motherboard
stopped all the ethernetwork hangs I have been experiencing:
ftp hangs, netperf hangs, ping -f hangs, and random hangs with 
light traffic.
Thanks for the indirect help.
